Wes Borland kicks off our ArtistFirst Collection Series. 

Auction is now live on the site at https://www.analogr.com/l/the-wes-borland-collection/640d27e5-2c35-48e8-bf7d-72c4a09db11f

Collection item highlights include his first Mesa Boogie Dual Rectifier used to record "Three Dollar Bill, Y'all", his Yamaha CV820WB Signature Artists Series Prototype Guitar, his Neotek Series 1 Console, his 12 String Guild Acoustic used for the 9/11 Heroes Tribute & Pink Floyd cover of “Wish You Were Here" performance, his original green touring flight case with custom artwork used in Limp Bizkit, various recording guitars, stage clothing, and oil paintings.

Wes is a guitar pioneer navigating the worlds of metal, prog, and rock with a unique and unmatched style that has made him one of the most visible guitarists of his generation.

Borland was voted number 37 in Total Guitar's Top 100 Guitarists of All Time, has won the Riff Lord award at the Metal Hammer Golden Gods Awards 2018 held at indigo at The O2 in London, and been nominated for 3 Grammy Awards. Borland is known for his sonic experimentation and elaborate visual appearance. He is also a visual artist being known for his oil paintings and visual creations for his musical projects.  He has become the guitarist's guitarist.

Wes Borland is best know as the guitarist and backing vocalist of the rap metal band Limp Bizkit, the lead vocalist and guitarist of the alternative and industrial rock band Black Light Burns, and the co-founder of experimental metal band Big Dumb Face. Wes has played for or collaborated with Danny Elfman, The Crystal Method, TechN9ne, From First To Last, Filter, Jonathan Davis, etc.

Hot as the hinges of hades in Austria today!

Thanks to everyone who came out to our third visit to Europe this year. Our London show was especially memorable! We’re so grateful. Cheers. See ya next year! US, Australia, New Zealand, and Japan coming up.

Our last show in the US this year was the @aftershockfestival and it was a delight. This was also my gal @aliejoboxblock ‘s hometown show of Sacramento so we were loaded with friends and family onstage. I want to thank @dannywimmer @mike_tempesta_artist_relations at @officialjacksonguitars for guitars and EVH amplification - @ernieball for all the strings @prsguitars for all of the support and custom work on my 4 strings especially - @seymourduncanpickups  and my band mates and crew for keeping this thing going for almost 30 years now. We’re so excited to return to Japan, New Zealand, and Australia in November/December. This year has been incredible. Thanks to all of you for coming out to the shows and making all of this so fun! Cheers! #limpbizkit @limpbizkit
@limpbizkit Tokyo night 1 was amazing! Doing it again tonight then off to New Zealand tomorrow! Photos by @joecupertino and @saylasugardrop
Tokyo night 2!

This was the development process for the new stage look. From first sketch to sculpting and molding/casting/painting/grinding etc. @aliejoboxblock really helped me out on this one with pivoting to solve problems and come up with new solutions/ be a sounding board. I had the buffalo teeth to make the entire lower portion of the helmet but Japan and New Zealand have laws on importing animal products, so I cast 250 buffalo teeth out of resin which ended up being a plus because the material is lighter. The last photo is me repainting a new jacket today in Auckland because the fabric markers I used bled with sweat and were a complete fail. I don’t usually show the process this much but there have been questions about this one in particular so here ya go. Also shout out to @adelemildred for throwing me some advice from across the pond. Cheers!

A gigantic Happy Birthday to my favorite person of all time. @aliejoboxblock !!! Thank you for being the most supportive person and best friend and main squeeze and everything over the last 5 years! You’re the best. I’m sorry I’m not there for it!
